1
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:37,600
Make way.

2
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:38,399
Coming through, coming through.

3
00:00:38,439 --> 00:00:39,799
We're bringing in a washing machine!

4
00:00:41,359 --> 00:00:42,079
A washing machine!

5
00:00:42,399 --> 00:00:42,840
Mom.

6
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:44,719
I'll go find a place to put it.

7
00:00:44,719 --> 00:00:45,679
Okay, okay.

8
00:00:46,119 --> 00:00:47,039
A washing machine.

9
00:00:47,240 --> 00:00:48,719
Why did you suddenly buy a washing machine?

10
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:50,399
It's so expensive.

11
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:51,759
We bought it specifically

12
00:00:51,840 --> 00:00:52,520
to prepare for later

13
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:54,320
when people come to propose a match

14
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:56,240
so we can find a well-off girl.

15
00:00:56,479 --> 00:00:58,799
Why prepare for the second son so early?

16
00:00:59,159 --> 00:01:01,320
This is for our eldest son.

17
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:04,519
The amount of money our eldest makes

18
00:01:04,879 --> 00:01:06,879
is beyond your imagination.

19
00:01:06,879 --> 00:01:08,480
Minjiang...

20
00:01:08,879 --> 00:01:10,480
Anyway, in the future, our family

21
00:01:10,680 --> 00:01:12,799
will have a washing machine, a fridge...

22
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:16,000
the three, six, and eight major items.

23
00:01:16,079 --> 00:01:17,799
We'll have them all eventually.

24
00:01:17,799 --> 00:01:19,840
Your Minjiang is so capable.

25
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:21,840
If you know any

26
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:23,159
girls from good backgrounds,

27
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:24,959
hurry up and introduce them to us.

28
00:01:25,079 --> 00:01:25,879
If they're too late,

29
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,599
they won't get through our door.

30
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:29,480
For sure, for sure.

31
00:01:29,719 --> 00:01:31,159
Definitely.

32
00:01:32,719 --> 00:01:33,599
A while ago,

33
00:01:33,719 --> 00:01:35,480
weren't they so poor they were being chased for debt?

34
00:01:36,719 --> 00:01:38,120
Putting up a front.

35
00:01:39,519 --> 00:01:40,200
Wang Shulan.

36
00:01:40,719 --> 00:01:41,400
You're always muttering over there.

37
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,319
What are you saying?

38
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,319
I didn't say anything.

39
00:01:45,719 --> 00:01:46,680
Didn't say anything?

40
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:47,640
I clearly heard you.

41
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:49,319
Some people just can't stand seeing others do well.

42
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:50,719
Zheng

43
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,079
Min

44
00:01:52,519 --> 00:01:53,040
jiang.

45
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:57,480
I think he's actually quite nice.

46
00:01:59,799 --> 00:02:01,760
Sis, there's nothing going on between Zheng Minjiang and me.

47
00:02:04,799 --> 00:02:06,480
I didn't say it was Zheng Minjiang.

48
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:11,919
Yingrong.

49
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:14,759
I've been there before.

50
00:02:15,639 --> 00:02:17,800
If you want to settle down,

51
00:02:18,879 --> 00:02:19,599
I think

52
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:21,159
he really is a decent guy.

53
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,560
No, no, no.

54
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:24,759
Zheng Minjiang doesn't like me.

55
00:02:25,319 --> 00:02:26,280
And in his eyes,

56
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,919
I've always been a troublemaker.

57
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:29,479
How could that be?

58
00:02:34,919 --> 00:02:37,159
Sis, don't you know?

59
00:02:37,719 --> 00:02:40,199
Zheng Minjiang has always liked you.

60
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:43,039
He even wrote you a love letter before.

61
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:45,960
Oh, that matter.

62
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:47,400
I know about it.

63
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:49,719
But that love letter

64
00:02:49,719 --> 00:02:51,520
wasn't written for me at all.

65
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,159
It was written for you.

66
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:58,080
Sis, stop joking.

67
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:01,039
He gave it to me personally to pass on to you.

68
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:02,800
Why would I lie to you?

69
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,560
He told me himself.

70
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,360
He said he finally

71
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:08,080
worked up the courage to give you the letter,

72
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:10,360
but you just took it and ran off.

73
00:03:10,919 --> 00:03:12,319
He was afraid of a misunderstanding,

74
00:03:12,319 --> 00:03:13,560
so he asked me to tell you.

75
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:14,680
But then

76
00:03:15,039 --> 00:03:17,199
something happened to his dad that very night.

77
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:20,520
You know what happened after that.

78
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:22,840
Our families were at each other's throats.

79
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,680
I saw that you two never got along,

80
00:03:26,159 --> 00:03:27,479
so I never mentioned this.

81
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:31,840
Wait a second.

82
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:33,360
I'll show you something.

83
00:03:38,639 --> 00:03:40,039
Good thing I didn't lose it.

84
00:03:42,039 --> 00:03:42,639
Look here.

85
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:44,199
On this...

86
00:03:44,719 --> 00:03:46,439
although he didn't write a name,

87
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:48,159
look at the content of the letter.

88
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:49,879
Here.

89
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:53,599
Cheerful, sunny.

90
00:03:54,039 --> 00:03:54,680
And here.

91
00:03:55,759 --> 00:03:57,199
Independent and strong.

92
00:03:58,240 --> 00:03:59,039
This...

93
00:03:59,479 --> 00:04:01,240
what does this have to do with me?

94
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:02,400
See for yourself.

95
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:29,639
Those girls,

96
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:31,879
seeing my family's situation,

97
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,480
all want to marry in.

98
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:34,439
And those

99
00:04:34,519 --> 00:04:36,759
who are breaking their necks to get in.

100
00:04:37,759 --> 00:04:39,759
And those matchmakers,

101
00:04:39,839 --> 00:04:41,279
seeing I have ten thousand yuan,

102
00:04:41,399 --> 00:04:42,920
no matter the match,

103
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,720
they can talk it into happening.

104
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,319
Our eldest,

105
00:04:47,319 --> 00:04:49,519
second, and third sons' marriages,

106
00:04:49,519 --> 00:04:50,879
were settled in a snap.

107
00:04:51,519 --> 00:04:52,079
Mom,

108
00:04:53,519 --> 00:04:54,079
look.

109
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,000
Isn't that Minjiang's runaway wife?

110
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:58,279
Mom, I'm back.

111
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:03,319
Yang Liu, why have you shown up again?

112
00:05:04,079 --> 00:05:04,639
Mom,

113
00:05:04,759 --> 00:05:06,199
what are you saying?

114
00:05:06,519 --> 00:05:08,120
I married Minjiang, after all.

115
00:05:08,279 --> 00:05:09,639
This is my home.

116
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:12,920
Didn't you take the money and run?

117
00:05:13,079 --> 00:05:15,240
Mom, what kind of talk is that?

118
00:05:15,439 --> 00:05:16,519
Getting married,

119
00:05:16,519 --> 00:05:18,720
doesn't the groom's family have to pay?

120
00:05:19,839 --> 00:05:20,920
Besides,

121
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:25,439
I went back to my parents' for so long,

122
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,879
didn't you miss me at all?

123
00:05:27,519 --> 00:05:29,759
Mom, Minjiang missed me a lot.

124
00:05:29,879 --> 00:05:32,480
He wrote every day asking when I'd return.

125
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:33,720
From now on,

126
00:05:33,839 --> 00:05:35,199
we'll live a good life together.

127
00:05:37,199 --> 00:05:39,439
You're still willing to live with Minjiang?

128
00:05:39,879 --> 00:05:40,920
Of course I am.

129
00:05:41,319 --> 00:05:42,160
I'm not.

130
00:05:44,879 --> 00:05:45,519
Minjiang.

131
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:48,120
What are you doing here again?

132
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:49,839
Didn't I make it clear

133
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,199
not to come looking for me?

134
00:05:51,519 --> 00:05:53,600
Minjiang, are you still angry?

135
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,000
We are not husband and wife.

136
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:57,480
We never registered the marriage.

137
00:05:57,839 --> 00:05:59,600
You are not legally my wife.

138
00:06:00,279 --> 00:06:02,399
But the villagers all attended the banquet.

139
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:03,519
I don't believe

140
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:05,680
that every single one of them is blind.

141
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:07,600
Minjiang.

142
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:10,879
Young couples fight, but lovers' quarrels are soon mended.

143
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:11,759
Mom,

144
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:13,120
this matter,

145
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,240
don't get involved.

146
00:06:16,439 --> 00:06:17,120
Minjiang.

147
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:18,680
I don't care what you came for this time,

148
00:06:19,279 --> 00:06:20,040
but I advise you,

149
00:06:21,399 --> 00:06:23,519
don't try to scheme against our family.

150
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,279
Get out.

151
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:37,519
Minjiang,

152
00:06:37,959 --> 00:06:40,560
I know we had misunderstandings before.

153
00:06:40,839 --> 00:06:42,199
The past was my fault.

154
00:06:42,399 --> 00:06:43,199
Look, I...

155
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,600
Minjiang!

156
00:06:48,319 --> 00:06:49,279
What are you looking at?

157
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:51,480
If it weren't for your money,

158
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:52,920
who would want to come back to you?

159
00:06:53,319 --> 00:06:54,600
It doesn't matter if you don't admit it.

160
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:56,079
As long as others think

161
00:06:56,079 --> 00:06:57,920
I'm the Zheng family's daughter-in-law, that's enough.

162
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,480
A woman like this,

163
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:03,399
whoever marries her is unlucky.

164
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:04,920
Minjiang,

165
00:07:05,399 --> 00:07:06,240
that Yang Liu,

166
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,680
she was wrong before.

167
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,399
But now that she's back,

168
00:07:09,399 --> 00:07:10,920
if she settles down with you,

169
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,759
it might still be okay.

170
00:07:13,279 --> 00:07:13,879
Mom,

171
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:15,879
ever since Dad passed away,

172
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:17,920
I've listened to whatever you said.

173
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,319
Because I'm the eldest,

174
00:07:20,199 --> 00:07:21,720
I have to set an example for my brothers.

175
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:24,240
But this obedient Zheng Minjiang

176
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:26,319
is not the real me.

177
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:34,319
Mom

178
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:35,920
I've figured it out

179
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,279
I can't be like I was before

180
00:07:39,439 --> 00:07:40,879
You say you're arranging a marriage for me

181
00:07:41,079 --> 00:07:41,879
and I just get married

182
00:07:42,519 --> 00:07:44,319
Whatever wife you arrange for me

183
00:07:44,519 --> 00:07:45,160
I just accept it

184
00:07:45,879 --> 00:07:46,759
And I certainly can't just listen to you

185
00:07:46,959 --> 00:07:48,240
telling me to get back with Yang Liu

186
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,519
and just get back with her

187
00:07:51,399 --> 00:07:51,879
Mom

188
00:07:52,279 --> 00:07:53,319
My own path

189
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:54,920
I decide for myself

190
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:57,279
I...

191
00:07:58,040 --> 00:08:00,519
I did that for your own good

192
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:02,279
What did I do wrong?

193
00:08:02,519 --> 00:08:03,959
You didn't do anything wrong

194
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,560
The fault isn't yours either

195
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:07,920
It's that Yang Liu and I aren't right for each other

196
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:09,199
On the wedding day

197
00:08:09,199 --> 00:08:10,720
she ran off with all the gift money

198
00:08:11,079 --> 00:08:11,720
Now that she's back

199
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:13,480
it's just because she sees our family has money

200
00:08:14,399 --> 00:08:15,240
How could I possibly act

201
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,920
like nothing ever happened

202
00:08:17,079 --> 00:08:18,480
and keep living with her?

203
00:08:21,279 --> 00:08:22,439
Is it that you...

204
00:08:22,759 --> 00:08:24,959
now that you're making money

205
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:27,560
want to find a better girl

206
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:29,240
and look down on her?

207
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:30,040
Yes

208
00:08:30,319 --> 00:08:31,240
That's exactly what I think

209
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,039
That's fine then

210
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,559
Yang Liu as a daughter-in-law

211
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:36,080
if you don't accept her, then don't

212
00:08:36,399 --> 00:08:37,279
You're right

213
00:08:37,519 --> 00:08:39,080
You haven't registered the marriage yet

214
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,679
so you aren't officially husband and wife

215
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:42,000
Even though we held the banquet

216
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,639
and the neighbors all saw it

217
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:46,679
but if there's a good girl

218
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:49,240
it doesn't matter what others say

219
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:51,159
Mom will block those rumors for you

220
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,759
But you have to promise Mom

221
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,360
if you look again

222
00:08:54,519 --> 00:08:57,720
you must find a very, very good girl

223
00:08:57,879 --> 00:08:59,600
a hundred times better than Yang Liu

224
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:01,480
Definitely better than her

225
00:09:02,559 --> 00:09:03,399
That's good then

226
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,360
But I have something to tell you

227
00:09:05,919 --> 00:09:07,919
You're at that factory now

228
00:09:07,919 --> 00:09:09,080
working as a technical consultant

229
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:12,279
You still need to bring your two brothers along

230
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:14,480
Ask that Factory Director Tang

231
00:09:15,279 --> 00:09:17,799
to arrange jobs for your two brothers

232
00:09:18,519 --> 00:09:19,080
Mom

233
00:09:19,919 --> 00:09:20,840
after all this talk

234
00:09:21,399 --> 00:09:23,679
you still want to arrange things your way

235
00:09:24,639 --> 00:09:25,320
Whether it's me

236
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:27,679
Haiyang, or Xiaochuan

237
00:09:27,919 --> 00:09:28,720
we are all the same

238
00:09:28,919 --> 00:09:30,919
We can all be responsible for our own actions

239
00:09:31,279 --> 00:09:32,600
How can that be okay?

240
00:09:32,799 --> 00:09:34,679
Can't let those two mess around

241
00:09:40,519 --> 00:09:41,960
You work pretty hard

242
00:09:42,279 --> 00:09:43,080
Reliable

243
00:09:43,879 --> 00:09:45,279
You're not bad for a creditor

244
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:46,720
You practice what you preach

245
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:48,279
not just ordering me to work

246
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:49,799
You're putting in more effort than me

247
00:09:50,799 --> 00:09:51,559
Because

248
00:09:51,799 --> 00:09:53,799
I always want to find something to do

249
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,320
Working is better than being idle

250
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:56,039
Exactly

251
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,279
I feel at peace when I'm working

252
00:09:58,600 --> 00:09:59,519
Fair enough

253
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:06,799
Here.

254
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:10,039
I was just thirsty. Thanks.

255
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:15,879
Wang Yingrong is seducing men again.

256
00:10:16,679 --> 00:10:18,679
You still want to look at that Wang Yingrong, don't you?

257
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:21,200
Look, who is that man next to her?

258
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:29,120
Is this the one who went to the labor camp?

259
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,200
The Zheng family's second son.

260
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,080
Zheng.

261
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,279
Zheng Haiyang.

262
00:10:33,519 --> 00:10:34,399
That Wang Yingrong.

263
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:36,399
She's even hooking up with an ex-convict.

264
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:39,360
A shameless woman and an ex-convict.

265
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,279
They're actually a good match.

266
00:10:41,039 --> 00:10:42,159
She caused me to lose my job.

267
00:10:42,879 --> 00:10:44,240
I'm not done with her in this lifetime.

268
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:49,639
Then let's not make life easy for her.

269
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:52,879
My fish isn't fishy.

270
00:10:53,039 --> 00:10:54,279
Unlike some people.

271
00:10:54,519 --> 00:10:55,679
Who are fishier than the fish.

272
00:10:56,399 --> 00:10:58,519
You know that Wang Yingrong, right?

273
00:10:58,919 --> 00:11:00,799
Heard she's now with that ex-convict.

274
00:11:00,799 --> 00:11:01,879
Hooked up together.

275
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:03,960
Wang Yingrong, the second child of the Wang family.

276
00:11:04,519 --> 00:11:05,080
Exactly.

277
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,720
Isn't the ex-convict the Zheng family's second son?

278
00:11:07,399 --> 00:11:08,480
The two of them hooked up.

279
00:11:08,879 --> 00:11:09,879
Exactly.

280
00:11:10,039 --> 00:11:11,840
I think they both smell just as fishy.

281
00:11:12,039 --> 00:11:13,519
Anyone who sees them would turn away.

282
00:11:15,639 --> 00:11:17,159
What rumors are you spreading here?

283
00:11:17,399 --> 00:11:18,240
My second son.

284
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:20,759
Would never hook up with that Wang Yingrong.

285
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:23,240
Whether they hooked up or not,

286
00:11:23,399 --> 00:11:25,679
I'm afraid you'll have to go home and ask to know.

287
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:27,080
Exactly, exactly.

288
00:11:27,159 --> 00:11:28,279
Go back and ask.

289
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:30,320
Don't be unaware of the situation,

290
00:11:30,519 --> 00:11:32,799
And say "no" so decisively here.

291
00:11:33,879 --> 00:11:35,240
Wait until I go back and ask clearly.

292
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:36,960
I'll tear your mouths apart.

293
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:41,279
Wang Yingrong.

294
00:11:41,799 --> 00:11:42,720
You come out here.

295
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:43,919
Wang Yingrong.

296
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:46,080
Did you seduce our Haiyang?

297
00:11:46,679 --> 00:11:47,320
Wang Yingrong.

298
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:48,879
Speak for yourself.

299
00:11:48,879 --> 00:11:49,840
You homewrecker.

300
00:11:50,279 --> 00:11:52,039
Why are you seducing my Haiyang?

301
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:53,879
Mom.

302
00:11:55,639 --> 00:11:56,720
What are you doing?

303
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,519
I heard people outside saying.

304
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:02,159
That you and Wang Yingrong are hooking up.

305
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:03,399
It makes me angry just hearing it.

306
00:12:03,679 --> 00:12:05,360
They are ruining your reputation.

307
00:12:05,799 --> 00:12:06,840
If it's about what they said,

308
00:12:07,399 --> 00:12:08,799
Why come back and scold Sister Yingrong?

309
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:11,720
I'm an ex-convict anyway.

310
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:13,240
Am I afraid of others ruining my reputation?

311
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,440
Getting involved with the Wang family.

312
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,639
Is worse than being an ex-convict.

313
00:12:17,919 --> 00:12:18,559
It won't do.

314
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:20,480
I'm going to find that Wang Yingrong today.

315
00:12:20,639 --> 00:12:21,919
And make her give me an explanation.

316
00:12:21,919 --> 00:12:22,360
Mom.

317
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:24,399
You heard wrong.

318
00:12:25,279 --> 00:12:26,639
The point of what they said was me.

319
00:12:26,879 --> 00:12:27,440
But.

320
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:29,000
But they clearly said.

321
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,200
You and Wang Yingrong.

322
00:12:30,519 --> 00:12:31,720
Do you think Wang Yingrong is stupid?

323
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:33,559
What do you mean?

324
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,519
Do you think with her conditions,

325
00:12:36,039 --> 00:12:37,360
She needs to find an ex-convict?

326
00:12:39,279 --> 00:12:40,559
Our two families are so close.

327
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:43,360
It's perfectly normal to exchange a few words when we meet.

328
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:45,519
Just don't worry about how others spread rumors.

329
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:47,919
Anyway, there is one fact in what they said that isn't wrong.

330
00:12:48,879 --> 00:12:50,080
I am just an ex-convict.

331
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:52,279
Son.

332
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,399
Don't think so much.

333
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,879
Even if I'm out, it doesn't change the fact.

334
00:12:57,879 --> 00:12:59,240
If I can't make something of myself,

335
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:01,240
I can't blame others for talking about me like this.

336
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:03,600
Forget it, forget it.

337
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:06,440
Don't worry about what those gossips say.

338
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:08,440
Don't take it to heart.

339
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:10,200
I won't take it to heart either.

340
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,240
Let's go, let's go home.

341
00:13:23,279 --> 00:13:25,440
Whose daughter lacks upbringing like that?

342
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:26,919
It's indecent.

343
00:13:27,519 --> 00:13:29,039
Alright, alright.

344
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:34,720
Mom.

345
00:13:35,519 --> 00:13:36,559
Little Sister.

346
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:43,120
Come back with me.

347
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:43,919
Hey.

348
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:45,039
Ying Tang.
